# Decentralized AI Knowledge Engine (Inspired by DeepTutor & memvid)

This plan outlines the architecture and implementation for a fully client-side, persistent knowledge system. The system runs in the browser via Rust + WebAssembly, using GitHub for identity and storage.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **GitHub OAuth (PKCE)**: Since there is NO backend, we must use GitHub's OAuth with PKCE. My plan assumes a pure client-side approach.
>
> **LLM API Keys**: The user must provide an LLM API key (OpenAI/Anthropic/Google). This will be stored securely in the browser's `localStorage`.
>
> **WASM Performance**: Large wiki operations might be slow over the network. We will implement a "staged commit" pattern to minimize roundtrips.

## 1. System Architecture (Mermaid)

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Browser (Rust + WASM)"
        UI[UI Layer - HTML/JS/CSS]
        Core[Core Logic - Rust Engine]
        Agents[Multi-Agent System]
        GH_Client[GitHub API Client]
        Memvid[memvid Session Engine]
        Search[Vector/BM25 Search]
    end

    subgraph "GitHub (Database & Identity)"
        Repo["user-private-repo/"]
        Raw["/raw/ (Immutable Sources)"]
        Wiki["/wiki/ (LLM-Maintained)"]
        Schema["/schema/ (LLM OS)"]
        History["/memvid/ (Session Artifacts)"]
    end

    subgraph "External AI Services"
        LLM[LLM API - Claude/GPT/Gemini]
    end

    UI <--> Core
    Core <--> Agents
    Agents <--> GH_Client
    Agents <--> LLM
    GH_Client <--> Repo
    Core <--> Memvid
    Memvid --> History
```

## 2. GitHub Repository Structure

The user's knowledge base will be a private GitHub repository with the following structure:

```text
/
├── raw/                # Source files (PDF, MD, TXT, etc.)
│   └── research_paper_v1.pdf
├── wiki/               # The Primary Database (Markdown)
│   ├── index.md        # Entry point for LLM/User
│   ├── log.md          # Chronological record
│   ├── entities/       # People, places, organizations
│   ├── concepts/       # Theories, ideas
│   └── topics/         # Broad subject areas
├── schema/             # System Instructions (Immutable-ish)
│   ├── AGENTS.md       # Agent definitions & personas
│   └── WORKFLOWS.md    # Ingest, Lint, Query protocols
└── memvid/             # Session Memory (.json / .mv2)
    └── session-2024-04-07.json
```

## 3. Wiki File Schema Examples

### Concept Page (`/wiki/concepts/distributed_consensus.md`)
```markdown
---
title: Distributed Consensus
last_updated: 2024-04-07
tags: [systems, algorithms]
citations: [raw/paxos_made_simple.pdf]
---

# Distributed Consensus

## Summary
The process of reaching agreement on a single data value among distributed processes or systems.

## Related
- [[paxos]]
- [[raft]]
- [[byzantine_fault_tolerance]]

## Context
Extracted from "Paxos Made Simple". It is critical for maintaining consistency in decentralized systems.
```

## 4. Rust Crate Design

The application will be structured as a workspace with several specialized crates:

- **`core`**: Main orchestrator, state management, and WASM entry points.
- **`agents`**: Implementations of Ingest, Maintainer, Query, Linking, and Lint agents.
- **`github`**: Wrapper for GitHub REST/GraphQL API.
- **`wiki`**: Markdown parsing, metadata extraction, and inter-linking logic.
- **`memvid`**: Integration with the `memvid` library for session recording.
- **`ui`**: Minimal JS/HTML for the chat and wiki browser interface.

## 5. End-to-End User Flow

1.  **Auth**: User logs in with GitHub (PKCE).
2.  **Selection**: User selects an existing "Knowledge Repo" or creates a new one.
3.  **Ingest**:
    - User uploads `article.pdf`.
    - `github` crate pushes it to `/raw/`.
    - `Ingest Agent` reads the file.
    - `Wiki Maintainer Agent` identifies multiple pages to create/update.
    - `Linking Agent` ensures `index.md` and related pages are interlinked.
    - `github` crate performs a single multi-file commit to `/wiki/`.
4.  **Query**:
    - User asks questions, `Query Agent` scans `/wiki/index.md`, retrieves pages.
5.  **Session End**:
    - `memvid` crate generates session artifact and commits it.

## 6. Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **Unit Tests (Rust)**: Test markdown parsing and inter-linking logic.
- **WASM Tests**: Run `wasm-pack test` in a headless browser.

### Manual Verification
- Deploy to GitHub Pages.
- Authenticate and perform a full ingestion cycle.
- Verify the repo structure.
